{/* HERO */}

Ministry of Earth Sciences · CMLRE · Kochi

AI-Driven Unified Data Platform for{" "} Oceanographic, Fisheries & Biodiversity Insights

A cloud-ready, intelligent digital backbone that unifies oceanographic, fisheries, taxonomic, otolith and molecular (eDNA) data into one platform for ecosystem modelling and sustainable fisheries management.

Get Started (Login) View Features
Oceanography Fisheries Molecular Biodiversity AI & Data Platform
{/* right info card */}

Why this platform?

CMLRE manages massive, siloed datasets: physical, chemical and biological oceanography, fish abundance and taxonomy, otolith morphology, and environmental DNA (eDNA). Integrating these streams is critical for:

  • Real-time ecosystem health monitoring
  • Predicting fish distribution & stock dynamics
  • Evidence-based conservation & blue economy planning
{/* CORE CAPABILITIES */}

Core Capabilities

The AI-driven platform will act as a national marine data backbone for India, enabling cross-domain analytics and decision support.

Unified Data Ingestion

Automated pipelines to ingest structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data from oceanographic surveys, fisheries, taxonomy, otolith labs, and molecular biology labs.

Metadata & Standards

Internationally accepted formats (e.g., OBIS/GBIF, Darwin Core) with rich metadata and ontology-driven tagging for seamless discovery and reuse.

AI Analytics & Modelling

Machine learning models to correlate ocean parameters with biodiversity, predict species distributions, and flag anomalies in ecosystem health.

Interactive Visualisation

Dashboards for oceanographic trends, fisheries indices, taxonomic distributions, otolith shapes, and eDNA-based species detections.

{/* SPECIALISED MODULES */}

Specialised Scientific Modules

Taxonomy & Species ID

Manage reference taxonomic catalogues, link voucher specimens, images and sequences, and support AI-assisted species identification.

Otolith Morphology

Upload and visualise otolith images, extract shape descriptors, and run morphometric analyses for stock structure and life-history inference.

Molecular & eDNA Hub

Store barcode & eDNA sequencing runs, perform species matching, and map biodiversity patterns across space and time.

{/* CTA */}

Build the next-generation marine data backbone for India

Empower scientists, conservationists, and policymakers with a unified platform for holistic marine ecosystem assessment.
